modules.description: Handles error code translation between system-specific representations and human-readable messages. Works with error codes and exception types from the Unix module, particularly Unix.Unix_error. Converts obscure error codes like Unix.EUNKNOWNERR into descriptive strings, improving diagnostics on Windows and other platforms.

Converts Windows error codes to their corresponding human-readable string representations. Works with the Win_error_t.t type, which encapsulates error code values. Used to generate error messages for system-level failures in Windows application logging.

Provides functions to convert Unix errors into Windows-specific error representations and format them as human-readable strings. Works with Unix.error and a custom error type `t` that encapsulates Windows error codes. Used to decode unknown Unix errors into meaningful Windows error messages on Windows systems.

Provides functions to create, inspect, and convert Windows error codes into descriptive strings. Works with the `t` type, which represents error codes from the Windows API. Used to translate system call failures into human-readable messages for debugging and logging.

Converts an integer to a specific error type, returning None for invalid values. Works with the Win_error_t.t type, which represents Windows error codes. Used to safely map system error numbers to typed error representations in Windows API interactions.
